result.execSummary:
The defendant Vincent Te was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Vincent Te in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  William P. Dockry appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.

Defendant Vincent Te in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Porchia Sharese Lewand appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 15 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 20 days in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No VIOLENT contact with victim Bernia L.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay the DNA and DV surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
-Court WAIVED all other court costs, fees, and surcharges due to inability to pay.
-Provide DNA Sample.

Filed: 
-Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief
-Memorandum of Conditions of Probation
-Letter from defendant

Probation Review Hearing in branch 24.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for June 24, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
JusticePoint Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Defendant Vincent Te in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Sarah Zwach appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defense requesting modification of the No Contact order to a No Violent Contact order. Court orders the No Violent Contact order with the victim. Case remains set for Sentencing on 4/5/2016 at 1:30 pm. Case adjourned to branch 24.
Per defense request, case scheduled for a Hearing on a No Contact Order. Parties notified.

Defendant Vincent Te in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Porchia Sharese Lewand appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Case set for Final Pretrial. Parties have reached a resolution. Court VACATES Jury Trial date. 

AS TO COUNT 1
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence. 

AS TO COUNT 2
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on motion of the state, court ordered count 2 Dismissed, But Read In. 

Filed, Notice of Right to Seek Post Conviction Relief. 

Court grants supervised third party contact with defendant's child.

Case adjourned to branch 24 for Sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 5, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed, Justice Point Report.

Defendant Vincent Te in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Porchia Sharese Lewand appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defense requests Final Pretrial and Jury Trial dates. Court grants defense request. Case adjourned to branch 24.  Final pre-trial scheduled for March 8, 2016 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for April 6, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed, Justice Point Report.

Defendant to have no contact with: B.A.L. DOB: 4/17/93
